hands_on_practices.solution:
1. The Yukawa interaction in the vacuum becomes
$$\mathcal{L}_{Yukawa}\supset -y_t\bigl(\bar Q_L\tilde H\bigr)t_R + \text{h.c.}
=-y_t\left(\bar t_L\,\frac{v}{\sqrt2}\,t_R\right)+\text{h.c.}.$$
2. Combine the chiral fields into the Dirac spinor $t=t_L+t_R$ to obtain the mass term
$$\mathcal{L}_{mass}=-m_t\,\bar t t=-y_t\frac{v}{\sqrt2}\bigl(\bar t_L t_R+\bar t_R t_L\bigr).$$
3. By matching coefficients,
$$m_t=\frac{y_t\,v}{\sqrt2}.$$
4. Compute the parameter
$$\kappa=\frac{v^2y_t^2}{m_t^2}
=\frac{v^2y_t^2}{\bigl(\frac{y_tv}{\sqrt2}\bigr)^2}
=\frac{v^2y_t^2}{\frac{y_t^2v^2}{2}}
=2.$$
